Blocks.childText: PEORIA. C. M. 113 Heavenly Dove. Closer Walk. Morning Prayer. 1 Come, Holy Spirit, heavenly Dove, 1 Oh, for a closer walk with God, 1 Lord, in the morning thou shalt With all thy quick'ning powers; A calm and heavenly frame! My voice ascending high; [hear Kindle a flame of sacred love A light to shine upon the road To thee will I direct my prayer, In these cold hearts of ours. That leads me to the Lamb! To thee lift up mine eye: 2 Father, and shall we ever live 2 The dearest idol I have known, 2 Up to the hills where Christ is gone At this poor dying rate- Whate'er that idol be, To plead for all his saints: Our love SO faint, SO cold to thee, Help me to tear it from thy throne, Presenting, at the Father's throne, And thine to us SO great? And worship only thee. Our songs and our complaints. 3 Come, Holy Spirit, heavenly Dove, 3 So shall my walk be close with God, 3 Oh, may thy Spirit guide my feet With all thy quick'ning powers; Calm and serene my frame; In ways of righteousness; Come, shed abroad a Savior's love, So purer light shall mark the road Make every path of duty straight, And that shall kindle ours. That leads me to the Lamb. And plain before my face! CAMBRIDGE. C. M. Not Ashamed. Abundant Mercies. Joyful Sound. 1 I'm not ashamed to own my Lord, 1 When all thy mercies, oh, my God, 1 Salvation oh, the joyful sound Or to defend his cause: My rising soul surveys, What pleasure to our ears! Maintain the honor of his word, Transported with the view, I'm lost A sovereign balm for every wound, The glory of his cross. In wonder, love, and praise! A cordial for our fears. 2 Firm as his throne his promise 2 Through every period of my life 2 Salvation ! let the echo fly And he can well secure [stands, Thy goodness I'll pursue; The spacious world around, What I've committed to his hands, And after death. in distant worlds, While all the armies of the sky Till the decisive hour. The pleasing theme renew. Conspire to raise the sound. 3 Then he will own my worthless 3 Through all eternity to thee 3 Salvation o thou bleeding Lamb! Before his Father's face, [name A grateful song I'll raise; To thee the praise belongs; And in the New Jerusalem But, oh ! eternity's too short Salvation shall inspire our hearts, Appoint my soul a place. To utter all thy praise. And dwell upon our tongues. 8
